cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper presents a computational model for simulating traffic flow in an arterial network and discusses the calibration and experiments conducted using the model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses optimization techniques (quadratic programming, linear programming) to calibrate the model and conduct experiments, which can be considered as AI-related methods. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control and optimization of traffic flow in an arterial network, which can be seen as a system that needs to be controlled and optimized. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the simulation of traffic flow in a network (arterial network), which can be considered as a type of networking. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses information (flow conservation identities, field measurements) to calibrate the model and evaluate its performance, which can be seen as related to information theory.
